1
00:00:30,574 --> 00:00:35,971
[UPBEAT MUSIC]

2
00:00:35,971 --> 00:00:40,541
[UPBEAT MUSIC]

3
00:01:02,171 --> 00:01:05,000
...SO, UM, THERE MIGHT BE
A FEW BARNACLES ON IT

4
00:01:05,043 --> 00:01:06,784
BUT I'VE BEEN ASSURED
BY SOME OF YOU

5
00:01:06,828 --> 00:01:09,395
THAT HAVE HAD MORE RECENT
SAILING EXPERIENCE THAN I HAVE

6
00:01:09,439 --> 00:01:11,659
THAT IN JUST A MATTER
OF A FEW HOURS

7
00:01:11,702 --> 00:01:14,313
OUT ON THE
STRAITS OF JUAN DE FUCA

8
00:01:14,357 --> 00:01:17,142
AND ALL THOSE BARNACLES
WILL SLOUGH OFF

9
00:01:17,186 --> 00:01:20,058
AND IT'LL BE SMOOTH SAILING
FROM THERE ON OUT

10
00:01:20,102 --> 00:01:23,235
ACROSS THE PACIFIC TO
THE HAWAIIAN ISLANDS.

11
00:01:23,279 --> 00:01:28,501
AND AFTER SOME RECUPERATIVE TIME
ON OAHU, MAYBE ON TO KAUAI,

12
00:01:28,545 --> 00:01:31,156
AND THEN I'LL SET MY SIGHTS
TO MOVE A LITTLE FURTHER WEST

13
00:01:31,200 --> 00:01:32,941
AND I'M NOT SURE
WHETHER IT'S GONNA BE JAPAN

14
00:01:32,984 --> 00:01:36,118
OR THE PHILIPPINES.

15
00:01:36,161 --> 00:01:37,946
MAYBE I'LL WANT TO UH,

16
00:01:37,989 --> 00:01:41,210
MAYBE I'LL WANT TO
SAIL AROUND THE WORLD!

17
00:01:41,253 --> 00:01:46,128
[LAUGHTER]

18
00:01:46,171 --> 00:01:47,520
AND I CAN ASSURE YOU,

19
00:01:47,564 --> 00:01:50,393
TAKING SPECIAL PRECAUTIONS
IN INSPECTING MY BOAT

20
00:01:50,436 --> 00:01:52,090
AND PROVISIONING MY BOAT.

21
00:01:52,134 --> 00:01:55,616
I'VE STOCKED
THE BOAT THOROUGHLY.

22
00:01:55,659 --> 00:02:00,098
THE FACT IS, I HAVE 480,000
CALORIES OF FOODSTUFF ON BOARD.

23
00:02:00,142 --> 00:02:01,970
I'VE CALCULATED
THAT WOULD LAST ME

24
00:02:02,013 --> 00:02:05,321
SOMETHING ON THE ORDER
OF ALMOST TWO MONTHS.

25
00:02:07,889 --> 00:02:11,153
I'VE HAD AT LEAST HALF A DOZEN
PRACTICE SESSIONS HERE

26
00:02:11,196 --> 00:02:13,155
JUST RECENTLY OUT
IN THE BAY.

27
00:02:13,198 --> 00:02:16,288
AND I PRACTICE THINGS
LIKE SCANNING THE HORIZON

28
00:02:16,332 --> 00:02:17,855
AND THE FOREGROUND
LOOKING FOR DEBRIS

29
00:02:17,899 --> 00:02:20,510
THAT I DON'T WANT TO RUN OVER.

30
00:02:20,553 --> 00:02:23,034
AND ALSO, I'VE GOT A HANDBOOK.

31
00:02:23,078 --> 00:02:24,688
I BOUGHT A HANDBOOK.

32
00:02:24,732 --> 00:02:27,343
IT'S ALL ABOUT LIVING AT SEA
IN A RAFT.

33
00:02:27,386 --> 00:02:29,867
HOW TO SURVIVE IN AN EMERGENCY.

34
00:02:29,911 --> 00:02:34,611
I'VE EVEN GOT A GPS TO HELP ME
WITH MY CELESTIAL NAVIGATION.

35
00:02:34,655 --> 00:02:37,570
I'VE BEEN REALLY HONING
MY SKILLS AS A SAILOR

36
00:02:37,614 --> 00:02:39,181
AND THEY ARE JUST
A LITTLE BIT RUSTY

37
00:02:39,224 --> 00:02:43,576
BUT I'VE BEEN REAL PLEASED
WITH THE WAY THINGS ARE GOING.

38
00:02:43,620 --> 00:02:44,969
KEEP IN MIND,

39
00:02:45,013 --> 00:02:48,973
I HAVE LIVED ON THIS BOAT
FOR NEARLY 30 YEARS NOW

40
00:02:49,017 --> 00:02:51,497
AND WHEN YOU'RE CONFINED
TO 70 SQUARE FEET OVER 30 YEARS,

41
00:02:51,541 --> 00:02:53,108
YOU REALLY GET TO KNOW

42
00:02:53,151 --> 00:02:56,720
ALL THE LITTLE
NOOKS AND CRANNIES

43
00:02:56,764 --> 00:03:00,071
AND THEY BECOME REALLY
ALMOST A PART OF YOU.

44
00:03:00,115 --> 00:03:02,726
YOU KNOW, I KNOW WE ALL
HAVE CONCERNS ABOUT BRITT BUT,

45
00:03:02,770 --> 00:03:04,772
BY GOLLY, WE OUGHT TO BE
REALLY HAPPY FOR HIM.

46
00:03:04,815 --> 00:03:07,731
HE WORKED FOR
QUALITY AUTOMOTIVE SERVICE

47
00:03:07,775 --> 00:03:09,690
ALL OF HIS LIFE THAT I KNOWN.

48
00:03:09,733 --> 00:03:11,561
HELL, I'VE KNOWN HIM
FOR LONGER THAN YOU HAVE.

49
00:03:11,604 --> 00:03:14,042
PROBABLY 30-40 YEARS
THAT I'VE KNOWN HIM.

50
00:03:14,085 --> 00:03:16,131
YOU KNOW, THIS IS A GUY
THAT'S NEVER BEEN ANYWHERE.

51
00:03:16,174 --> 00:03:17,741
HE'S NEVER BEEN NORTH TO CANADA.

52
00:03:17,785 --> 00:03:19,264
HE'S NEVER BEEN TO MONTANA.

53
00:03:19,308 --> 00:03:22,006
I DON'T THINK HE'S EVEN
BEEN SOUTH TO OREGON.

54
00:03:22,050 --> 00:03:23,312
AND HERE HE'S UNDERGOING
THIS GREAT ADVENTURE.

55
00:03:23,355 --> 00:03:24,617
WE KNOW THE BOAT IS OLD

56
00:03:24,661 --> 00:03:27,490
AND, YOU KNOW,
IT'S NOT VERY WELL EQUIPPED

57
00:03:27,533 --> 00:03:29,144
BUT HE SEEMS TO BE ABLE
TO DEAL WITH THAT.

58
00:03:29,187 --> 00:03:31,668
HE WANTS TO GO AND I TELL YOU,
I'M SO HAPPY FOR HIM I JUST...

59
00:03:31,712 --> 00:03:33,757
[TALKING CONTINUES
IN BACKGROUND]

60
00:03:33,801 --> 00:03:35,759
BOB BURKHOLDER LOOKED LIKE
HE COULD TIP OVER DEAD

61
00:03:35,803 --> 00:03:37,282
AT ANY MOMENT

62
00:03:37,326 --> 00:03:39,632
BUT HE HAD MORE ENERGY THAN
ALMOST EVERYBODY I KNEW.

63
00:03:39,676 --> 00:03:42,940
[MUSIC]

64
00:03:42,984 --> 00:03:45,813
I'D ONLY MET BOB RECENTLY
IN MY SENIOR FITNESS CLASS.

65
00:03:45,856 --> 00:03:49,164
THAT'S RIGHT.
I'M A SENIOR.

66
00:03:49,207 --> 00:03:51,079
THAT DOESN'T QUITE
SIT RIGHT WITH ME EITHER

67
00:03:51,122 --> 00:03:55,692
BUT THAT'S WHAT THEY
CALL ME THESE DAYS.

68
00:03:55,736 --> 00:03:58,782
BOB ASKED ME
FOR A RIDE HOME ONE DAY

69
00:03:58,826 --> 00:04:00,131
WITH SOME STORY
ABOUT A FENDER-BENDER

70
00:04:00,175 --> 00:04:03,831
THAT LEFT HIS CAR IN THE SHOP.

71
00:04:03,874 --> 00:04:09,532
[BACKGROUND CONVERSATION]

72
00:04:09,575 --> 00:04:11,142
WELL, A RIDE HERE AND THERE

73
00:04:11,186 --> 00:04:14,885
QUICKLY TURNED INTO A FULL-TIME JOB IN A MATTER OF WEEKS.

74
00:04:14,929 --> 00:04:17,061
BUT IT DID GET ME OUT OF THE
HOUSE AND THE THING WAS,

75
00:04:17,105 --> 00:04:18,759
I SORT OF ENJOYED HIS COMPANY.

76
00:04:18,802 --> 00:04:20,673
HE TURNED OUT TO BE
A FASCINATING GUY

77
00:04:20,717 --> 00:04:22,240
AND I BECAME
PRETTY FOND OF HIM.

78
00:04:22,284 --> 00:04:23,807
STILL LAYING OVER
THE PILE OF ROCKS

79
00:04:23,851 --> 00:04:25,591
SO I ASSUME THE SHEEP
WERE STILL THERE.

80
00:04:25,635 --> 00:04:26,505
OH, YEAH.

81
00:04:26,549 --> 00:04:27,680
THAT'S THE WAY I SHOT THE SUCKER

82
00:04:27,724 --> 00:04:29,682
AND HE DROPPED
LIKE A SACK OF SHIT.

83
00:04:29,726 --> 00:04:30,988
I'LL BE DARNED.

84
00:04:31,032 --> 00:04:33,295
I JUST NAILED HIM RIGHT
TO THE SPOT AND I HAD TO

85
00:04:33,338 --> 00:04:34,818
BECAUSE HE'S RIGHT ON
THE EDGE OF THE CLIFF.

86
00:04:34,862 --> 00:04:35,906
YEAH.

87
00:04:35,950 --> 00:04:37,081
HAD HE KICKED ONCE,
HE'D BEEN OVER.

88
00:04:37,125 --> 00:04:38,343
WOW.

89
00:04:38,387 --> 00:04:39,649
SO I RAN DOWN AND JUMPED
ON TOP OF HIM AND --

90
00:04:39,692 --> 00:04:42,434
BOB'S TALES ABOUT
HUNTING MOOSE AND ELK

91
00:04:42,478 --> 00:04:44,523
AND BIG HORNED SHEEP IN MONTANA

92
00:04:44,567 --> 00:04:48,005
AND EVERYWHERE ELSE
YOU CAN THINK OF,

93
00:04:48,049 --> 00:04:51,922
PARACHUTING IN WORLD WAR II,
CRASHING PLANES IN ALASKA,

94
00:04:51,966 --> 00:04:55,752
AND ALL THAT STUFF,
IT'S JUST INCREDIBLE.

95
00:04:55,796 --> 00:04:57,841
HE'S WRITING MEMOIRS
OF SOME SORT

96
00:04:57,885 --> 00:05:01,540
AND FEELS COMPELLED
TO UPDATE ME ON HIS PROGRESS.

97
00:05:01,584 --> 00:05:03,151
I DON'T KNOW HOW MUCH
I BELIEVE EVERYTHING HE SAYS

98
00:05:03,194 --> 00:05:04,500
BUT IT SURE IS INTERESTING

99
00:05:04,543 --> 00:05:10,462
COMPARED TO MY
EXECUTIVE CAREER IN FINANCE.

100
00:05:10,506 --> 00:05:12,813
I RETIRED ABOUT SIX MONTHS AGO.

101
00:05:12,856 --> 00:05:14,510
AT LEAST THAT'S WHAT MY WIFE
AND I TOLD ALL OUR FRIENDS.

102
00:05:14,553 --> 00:05:16,642
TRUTH BE TOLD, I WAS EASED OUT

103
00:05:16,686 --> 00:05:20,385
WITH A VERY LARGE,
ENCOURAGING CHECK.

104
00:05:22,474 --> 00:05:25,129
I DO SORT OF MISS GOING
TO THE OFFICE EVERY MORNING

105
00:05:25,173 --> 00:05:28,785
AND JUST HAVING THAT
EVERY DAY ROUTINE.

106
00:05:28,829 --> 00:05:30,569
SO NOW EVERY MORNING
I GET UP AT THE REGULAR TIME

107
00:05:30,613 --> 00:05:32,397
AND SPEND A COUPLE HOURS
IN MY HOME OFFICE

108
00:05:32,441 --> 00:05:35,966
MANAGING MY RETIREMENT FUNDS.

109
00:05:38,099 --> 00:05:41,885
SO HAULING BOB
FROM PLACE TO PLACE

110
00:05:41,929 --> 00:05:44,888
HAS BECOME A CONSIDERABLE PART
OF MY DAILY ROUTINE.

111
00:05:44,932 --> 00:05:47,891
BOB HAS CHOIR PRACTICE ON
WEDNESDAYS AND FRIDAYS.

112
00:05:47,935 --> 00:05:50,633
SURPRISINGLY, HE'S A BASS.

113
00:05:50,676 --> 00:06:02,819
[CHOIR SINGING]
HALLELUJAH! HALLELUJAH!
HALLELUJAH! AMEN!

114
00:06:02,863 --> 00:06:10,653
[SINGING CONTINUES]

115
00:06:10,696 --> 00:06:13,917
TUESDAY AND THURSDAY
WAS MEN'S OATMEAL CLUB.

116
00:06:13,961 --> 00:06:16,441
YOU EVER HEARD OF
AN OATMEAL CLUB?

117
00:06:16,485 --> 00:06:17,790
IT'S AT THE SENIOR CENTER

118
00:06:17,834 --> 00:06:19,575
AND YOU SHOULD SEE
SOME OF THESE GUYS.

119
00:06:19,618 --> 00:06:20,663
BOB'S PRESIDENT!

120
00:06:20,706 --> 00:06:23,231
HE LEADS POST-MEAL DISCUSSIONS

121
00:06:23,274 --> 00:06:25,102
AND USUALLY THOSE
GET TRANSFORMED

122
00:06:25,146 --> 00:06:27,583
INTO ARGUMENTS OF SOME KIND.

123
00:06:27,626 --> 00:06:30,368
AND THERE'S BOB'S GIRLFRIEND,
CAROLYN.

124
00:06:30,412 --> 00:06:37,941
[MUSIC]

125
00:06:37,985 --> 00:06:40,465
I CAN'T IMAGINE WHERE HE GETS
THAT KIND OF ENERGY.

126
00:06:41,684 --> 00:06:43,512
BUT MONDAY NIGHTS
AT COREY'S CAFé

127
00:06:43,555 --> 00:06:45,122
DOWN BY THE HARBOR

128
00:06:45,166 --> 00:06:48,038
IS WHERE BOB SEEMS
TO FIT IN THE BEST.

129
00:06:48,082 --> 00:06:52,086
COREY WOULD CLOSE UP
AROUND 7:00.

130
00:06:52,129 --> 00:06:55,306
BUT HE'D KEEP THE PLACE
AVAILABLE TO THE OLD TIMERS.

131
00:06:55,350 --> 00:06:57,700
ALL GUYS LOCAL BUT I'D
NEVER MET THEM BEFORE.

132
00:06:57,743 --> 00:06:59,397
NO GIRLFRIENDS, NO WIVES,

133
00:06:59,441 --> 00:07:04,881
NO ORGANIZED AGENDA,
NO GUEST SPEAKERS.

134
00:07:04,925 --> 00:07:08,754
JUST GUYS BS'ING ABOUT
NOTHING IN PARTICULAR.

135
00:07:08,798 --> 00:07:11,192
I HAD DRIVEN BY COREY'S
THOUSANDS OF TIMES

136
00:07:11,235 --> 00:07:14,543
BUT I'D NEVER EVEN BEEN
IN THE PLACE UNTIL LAST MONTH.

137
00:07:14,586 --> 00:07:16,458
[LAUGHTER]

138
00:07:16,501 --> 00:07:17,676
TONIGHT AT COREY'S

139
00:07:17,720 --> 00:07:20,941
WAS COMPLETELY DIFFERENT
FROM THE NORM.

140
00:07:20,984 --> 00:07:23,291
ONE OF THESE GUYS
IS APPARENTLY LEAVING TOMORROW

141
00:07:23,334 --> 00:07:26,903
ON A LITTLE SAILBOAT FOR HAWAII.

142
00:07:26,947 --> 00:07:29,688
BOB HAD THIS BIG
SEND-OFF CELEBRATION.

143
00:07:29,732 --> 00:07:31,821
SLIDE SHOW.

144
00:07:31,864 --> 00:07:33,344
PLANNED COURSE DETAILS,

145
00:07:33,388 --> 00:07:37,305
LOCATIONS OF VISITS AND
A PAINFULLY LONG PRESENTATION

146
00:07:37,348 --> 00:07:40,047
ABOUT ALL THE PREP AND PLANNING THIS GUY HAD GONE THROUGH.

147
00:07:40,090 --> 00:07:43,267
CONGRATULATIONS!
[CHEERING AND APPLAUSE]

148
00:07:43,311 --> 00:07:44,790
THINK I'LL HAVE A GOOD TRIP.

149
00:07:44,834 --> 00:07:46,183
ALTHOUGH I THOUGHT
IT WAS PRETTY INCREDIBLE

150
00:07:46,227 --> 00:07:47,880
WHAT BRITT WAS DOING,
I WAS PRETTY SURE

151
00:07:47,924 --> 00:07:51,754
THIS WAS THE LAST TIME
WE'D EVER SEE THE GUY.

152
00:07:51,797 --> 00:07:54,104
- HAVE A GOOD TRIP THERE, BRITT.
- THANK YOU, FRANK.

153
00:07:54,148 --> 00:07:55,497
BOB WAS PARTICULARLY EXCITED

154
00:07:55,540 --> 00:07:56,846
BECAUSE BRITT HAD AGREED
TO LOAN HIM HIS TRUCK

155
00:07:56,889 --> 00:07:58,500
WHILE HE WAS GONE.

156
00:07:58,543 --> 00:08:01,242
AND THAT MEANT I WAS SOON TO BE RELEASED FROM MY DRIVING DUTIES.

157
00:08:03,461 --> 00:08:04,767
OF COURSE, IN THE MORNING

158
00:08:04,810 --> 00:08:08,901
WHEN I TOOK BOB DOWN
TO WAVE GOODBYE,

159
00:08:08,945 --> 00:08:10,164
EVERYTHING CHANGED.

160
00:08:11,817 --> 00:08:13,994
BRITT! HEY, BRITT!

161
00:08:21,262 --> 00:08:23,438
WHAT DO YOU MEAN
YOU'RE NOT GOING?

162
00:08:23,481 --> 00:08:26,223
GOOD GOD, BEN!
WE HAD THE SLIDESHOW LAST NIGHT.

163
00:08:26,267 --> 00:08:27,485
WE GOT EVERYBODY EXCITED
ABOUT YOU GOING

164
00:08:27,529 --> 00:08:29,487
AND NOW YOU'RE CRAPPING OUT!

165
00:08:29,531 --> 00:08:31,924
YOU KNOW,
I THINK YOU'RE A WIMP.

166
00:08:31,968 --> 00:08:33,143
I WAS HOPING -- GODDAMMIT! --

167
00:08:33,187 --> 00:08:34,536
I WAS HOPING YOU'RE
CHANGING YOUR LIFE!

168
00:08:34,579 --> 00:08:35,363
WAIT, WAIT, WAIT.

169
00:08:35,406 --> 00:08:36,973
- WHAT?
- HANG ON.

170
00:08:37,017 --> 00:08:40,542
LET'S GO GET A CUP OF COFFEE
AND COOL DOWN.

171
00:08:40,585 --> 00:08:44,241
WELL, THAT MIGHT BE
A GOOD IDEA.

172
00:08:44,285 --> 00:08:46,417
THAT DAMN SON OF A BITCH!

173
00:08:46,461 --> 00:08:47,940
- THANK YOU.
- YOU'RE WELCOME.

174
00:08:51,640 --> 00:08:52,858
WELL, IT WAS AN AMBITIOUS IDEA

175
00:08:52,902 --> 00:08:56,166
THAT JUST DIDN'T
COME TO FRUITION.

176
00:08:56,210 --> 00:08:57,428
DON'T GET TOO DOWN ON YOURSELF.

177
00:08:57,472 --> 00:08:59,561
THERE'S A BUNCH OF
ADVENTURES TO BE HAD.

178
00:08:59,604 --> 00:09:01,215
YOU KNOW?

179
00:09:01,258 --> 00:09:04,261
I MEAN, THERE'S ALWAYS A SILVER
LINING TO EVERY EXPERIENCE, SO.

180
00:09:04,305 --> 00:09:06,307
OH, THAT'S BULLSHIT.

181
00:09:06,350 --> 00:09:08,135
YOU KNOW, I'M NOT GOING
TO GLOSS OVER THIS THING.

182
00:09:08,178 --> 00:09:10,267
YOU STARTED SOMETHING,
YOU OUGHT TO FINISH IT.

183
00:09:10,311 --> 00:09:12,400
I THOUGHT I MADE
MYSELF CLEAR, BOB.

184
00:09:12,443 --> 00:09:15,142
I'M NOT GOING.
END OF STORY.

185
00:09:17,840 --> 00:09:20,408
SO WHAT ARE YOU
GOING TO DO NOW?

186
00:09:20,451 --> 00:09:21,974
OH, I HADN'T EVEN
THOUGHT ABOUT THAT.

187
00:09:22,018 --> 00:09:26,414
UH, I MAYBE COULD GET
MY OLD JOB BACK.

188
00:09:26,457 --> 00:09:30,766
THAT'S INCREDULOUS!
GOTCHA NO IMAGINATION?

189
00:09:30,809 --> 00:09:32,028
YOU WANT TO BE A GREASE MONKEY

190
00:09:32,072 --> 00:09:33,943
THE REST OF YOUR LIFE,
FOR CHRIST SAKES?

191
00:09:33,986 --> 00:09:35,684
MAYBE YOU OUGHT TO TAKE UP
THE GAME OF GOLF.

192
00:09:35,727 --> 00:09:38,426
I MEAN, YOU KNOW,
DO SOME RELAXING THINGS.

193
00:09:38,469 --> 00:09:39,688
THAT'S A STUPID GAME.

194
00:09:39,731 --> 00:09:42,821
WELL, I DON'T KNOW ABOUT GOLF.

195
00:09:42,865 --> 00:09:44,823
YOU KNOW,
THIS IS GOING NOWHERE.

196
00:09:44,867 --> 00:09:47,130
I STILL NEED TO USE YOUR TRUCK.

197
00:09:47,174 --> 00:09:49,741
[BACKGROUND TALKING]

198
00:09:49,785 --> 00:09:51,395
[MOTOR STARTS]
A STANDARD TRANSMISSION?

199
00:09:51,439 --> 00:09:52,396
YEAH, I KNOW.

200
00:09:52,440 --> 00:09:53,528
PAY ATTENTION.

201
00:09:53,571 --> 00:09:55,051
WHEN YOU DRIVE,
IT'S A FULL-TIME JOB.

202
00:09:55,095 --> 00:09:57,749
DON'T BE TALKING WITH
SOMEBODY OR DAYDREAMING.

203
00:09:57,793 --> 00:09:59,751
NO, I WANT TO THANK YOU
FOR THE USE OF IT

204
00:09:59,795 --> 00:10:02,754
AND I'LL PROMISE I'LL HAVE
IT BACK AT 8 O'CLOCK.

205
00:10:02,798 --> 00:10:04,060
HOW'S THAT? TONIGHT.

206
00:10:04,104 --> 00:10:06,454
OKAY, YOU GO AHEAD
AND TAKE ON OUT OF HERE.

207
00:10:06,497 --> 00:10:08,673
DON'T FORGET TO RELEASE
THE EMERGENCY BRAKE.

208
00:10:15,680 --> 00:10:23,166
[MOTOR ROARS AND CHUGS AWAY]

209
00:10:23,210 --> 00:10:37,354
[MUSIC]

210
00:10:52,587 --> 00:10:55,198
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]
HEY, BRITT?

211
00:10:57,244 --> 00:10:59,028
IT'S DAVE.

212
00:10:59,071 --> 00:11:01,770
I GOT A PHONE CALL HERE FOR YOU.
BOB WANTS TO TALK TO YOU.

213
00:11:05,295 --> 00:11:08,080
- BOB.
- BRITT, IS THAT YOU FINALLY?

214
00:11:08,124 --> 00:11:12,563
YEAH, YOU PROMISED TO BE BACK
SO I COULD HAVE THE PICKUP.

215
00:11:12,607 --> 00:11:13,999
WELL, I KNOW.

216
00:11:14,043 --> 00:11:14,957
BUT YOU KNOW, THINGS ARE
DIFFERENT NOW THAN THEY WERE

217
00:11:15,000 --> 00:11:19,048
AND I'M SORRY ABOUT THAT.

218
00:11:19,091 --> 00:11:20,484
WELL, GODDAMMIT,

219
00:11:20,528 --> 00:11:22,051
YOU SHOULD SHOW A LITTLE MORE
CONSIDERATION AND --

220
00:11:22,094 --> 00:11:24,967
YEAH, THIS IS UNUSUAL
CIRCUMSTANCES, BRITT.

221
