00:21:04,372 --> 00:21:06,330
UM, ARE YOU MARRIED?

449
00:21:06,374 --> 00:21:08,506
UH, NO, I'M NOT MARRIED.

450
00:21:08,550 --> 00:21:11,248
SO I GUESS YOU DON'T
HAVE ANY KIDS THEN, HUH?

451
00:21:11,292 --> 00:21:14,077
WELL, ACTUALLY,
I DON'T THINK SO.

452
00:21:14,121 --> 00:21:16,123
OH! [LAUGHS]

453
00:21:16,166 --> 00:21:18,603
WELL, WHAT DO YOU DO FOR WORK?

454
00:21:18,647 --> 00:21:22,956
UM. I WAS IN THE OIL BUSINESS.
I JUST RECENTLY RETIRED.

455
00:21:22,999 --> 00:21:26,089
IN FACT, TODAY IS MY
FIRST DAY OF RETIREMENT.

456
00:21:26,133 --> 00:21:27,177
OH, WELL, CONGRATULATIONS.

457
00:21:27,221 --> 00:21:29,832
WHAT DID YOU DO
IN THE OIL BUSINESS?

458
00:21:29,876 --> 00:21:32,269
I, UH, WAS IN
THE OIL BUSINESS?

459
00:21:32,313 --> 00:21:33,488
- MM-HM.
- MM-HM.

460
00:21:33,531 --> 00:21:34,402
AND?

461
00:21:34,445 --> 00:21:35,229
PRETTY SUCCESSFUL.

462
00:21:35,272 --> 00:21:36,143
AH, I SEE.

463
00:21:36,186 --> 00:21:37,361
AND I WAS REAL GOOD AT IT.

464
00:21:37,405 --> 00:21:39,233
I WAS OVER 30 YEARS
IN THE OIL BUSINESS,

465
00:21:39,276 --> 00:21:41,365
IN THE MARKETING END OF THINGS.

466
00:21:41,409 --> 00:21:42,453
I SEE.

467
00:21:42,497 --> 00:21:44,020
BECAME VERY, VERY GOOD AT IT.

468
00:21:44,064 --> 00:21:46,806
WELL, UH, I HEARD A RUMOR
THAT YOU WERE PLANNING A TRIP

469
00:21:46,849 --> 00:21:50,113
SO I GUESS BEING RETIRED
MAKES THAT EASIER, HUH?

470
00:21:50,157 --> 00:21:53,943
UM, YES. IT DOES.

471
00:21:53,987 --> 00:21:57,555
I'VE BEEN CONTEMPLATING A TRIP
TO THE ISLANDS IN MY BOAT.

472
00:21:57,599 --> 00:21:58,948
SOME PEOPLE CALL IT MY YACHT.

473
00:21:58,992 --> 00:22:00,123
OH, REALLY?

474
00:22:00,167 --> 00:22:01,864
ARE YOU TAKING FRIENDS
OR A CREW ALONG?

475
00:22:01,908 --> 00:22:04,214
NO, I'M NOT TAKING A CREW.

476
00:22:04,258 --> 00:22:05,868
I'M GOING TO SOLO IT THIS TIME.

477
00:22:05,912 --> 00:22:07,000
HMM.

478
00:22:07,043 --> 00:22:08,523
I LIKE CHALLENGES.

479
00:22:08,566 --> 00:22:10,612
WOW. SOUNDS LIKE
A REAL CHALLENGE TO ME.

480
00:22:10,655 --> 00:22:11,874
WHAT DO YOU DO

481
00:22:11,918 --> 00:22:13,049
IF YOU GET INTO TROUBLE
OR YOU GO OVERBOARD

482
00:22:13,093 --> 00:22:15,486
OR SOMETHING AND YOU'RE
ALL BY YOURSELF?

483
00:22:15,530 --> 00:22:20,404
[DEEP SIGH]
WELL, THAT'S A GOOD QUESTION.

484
00:22:25,192 --> 00:22:27,803
[GRUMBLES] OH, SHIT.
'SCUSE MY LANGUAGE.

485
00:22:27,847 --> 00:22:28,935
UH, WOULD YOU EXCUSE ME?

486
00:22:28,978 --> 00:22:30,066
SURE.

487
00:22:30,110 --> 00:22:31,198
QUICK ANSWER IS I CAN'T SWIM

488
00:22:31,241 --> 00:22:32,895
SO I DON'T KNOW
WHAT THE HELL I'LL DO.

489
00:22:32,939 --> 00:22:34,201
OH, WOW.

490
00:22:36,246 --> 00:22:38,379
MAN, YOU'RE LOOKING GOOD.

491
00:22:38,422 --> 00:22:41,208
LOOK AT THAT.
YOU GOT A TIE ON AND EVERYTHING.

492
00:22:41,251 --> 00:22:42,600
GOD DAMMIT, BOB.

493
00:22:42,644 --> 00:22:44,559
CAN'T YOU SEE I'M RIGHT IN
THE MIDDLE OF SOMETHING?

494
00:22:44,602 --> 00:22:45,603
WELL, I DIDN'T KNOW.

495
00:22:45,647 --> 00:22:47,170
WHAT THE HELL
IS GOING ON HERE?

496
00:22:47,214 --> 00:22:48,432
WE'RE GONNA HAVE WORDS BUT
WE'RE GONNA HAVE WORDS LATER.

497
00:22:48,476 --> 00:22:50,478
DO YOU UNDERSTAND THAT?

498
00:22:50,521 --> 00:22:52,088
WHAT ARE YOU MAD
ABOUT THE TRUCK NOW?

499
00:22:52,132 --> 00:22:53,524
I TRIED TO GET IN
TOUCH WITH YOU.

500
00:22:53,568 --> 00:22:55,744
COME HERE, I GOT SOME
GOOD NEWS FOR YOU. COME ON.

501
00:22:55,787 --> 00:22:57,180
I GOT TO TELL YOU THIS.
THIS IS EXCITING.

502
00:22:57,224 --> 00:22:57,833
COME HERE.

503
00:22:58,965 --> 00:23:00,923
SON OF A BITCH.

504
00:23:00,967 --> 00:23:02,794
MAN, I GOT MY BOOK PUBLISHED.

505
00:23:06,059 --> 00:23:07,843
UNBELIEVABLE.

506
00:23:07,887 --> 00:23:10,280
WELL, I KIND OF THOUGHT SO,
TOO, AT ONE TIME.

507
00:23:10,324 --> 00:23:12,587
I NEVER THOUGHT YOU
WERE EVEN GOING TO THINK ABOUT

508
00:23:12,630 --> 00:23:14,545
PUBLISHING SOMETHING LIKE THAT.

509
00:23:14,589 --> 00:23:15,895
YEAH.
I'M REALLY EXCITED.

510
00:23:15,938 --> 00:23:17,809
MUCH LESS ANYONE
WOULD PUBLISH IT.

511
00:23:17,853 --> 00:23:19,942
CONGRATULATIONS!
THIS IS REALLY WONDERFUL.

512
00:23:19,986 --> 00:23:20,987
WELL, THANK YOU VERY MUCH.

513
00:23:21,030 --> 00:23:21,944
THAT'S SUPERB.

514
00:23:21,988 --> 00:23:22,379
I APPRECIATE THAT.

515
00:23:22,423 --> 00:23:23,424
MMM.

516
00:23:25,034 --> 00:23:28,995
SO WHERE'S THAT HAPPENING?
NEW YORK? CHICAGO?

517
00:23:29,038 --> 00:23:30,474
UH NO, NO.

518
00:23:30,518 --> 00:23:32,389
IT'S A SMALL PUBLISHING OUTFIT
IN EVERETT.

519
00:23:32,433 --> 00:23:33,825
THEY SELL PUBLISHING.

520
00:23:33,869 --> 00:23:35,088
IN EVERETT. OH!

521
00:23:35,131 --> 00:23:38,178
THEY READ THE BOOK AND LIKED IT.

522
00:23:38,221 --> 00:23:40,832
OH, IT'S A VERY GOOD MEMOIR.

523
00:23:40,876 --> 00:23:44,184
I'LL BE ABLE TO GET IT INTO FIVE
OR SIX LOCAL BOOKSTORES EASY.

524
00:23:44,227 --> 00:23:46,882
HMM, THAT'S NICE.

525
00:23:46,926 --> 00:23:48,710
TWO OR THREE, AT LEAST.

526
00:23:48,753 --> 00:23:53,062
NOW, I JUST NEED THAT CHECK
 FOR $500 FOR DISTRIBUTION,

527
00:23:53,106 --> 00:23:55,064
YOU KNOW, SHIPPING AND HANDLING.

528
00:23:55,108 --> 00:23:56,979
YOU KNOW,
THAT SEEMS AWFUL HIGH.

529
00:23:57,023 --> 00:23:59,851
I WAS, YOU KNOW,
I'M ALREADY IN WHAT?

530
00:23:59,895 --> 00:24:01,418
TWENTY-FOUR HUNDRED BUCKS
FOR IT.

531
00:24:01,462 --> 00:24:02,854
I THOUGHT THAT
PRETTY WELL DID IT

532
00:24:02,898 --> 00:24:04,595
AS FAR AS PUBLISHING
AND EDITING AND --

533
00:24:04,639 --> 00:24:09,296
WELL, THE $500 COVERS SOME OF
THE PHOTOSHOP WORK WE HAD TO DO.

534
00:24:09,339 --> 00:24:11,559
THE IMAGE OF THE PLANE WAS
A LITTLE FUZZY --

535
00:24:11,602 --> 00:24:13,169
YEAH.

536
00:24:13,213 --> 00:24:14,344
AND WE HAD TO TAKE THE FUZZ OUT.

537
00:24:14,388 --> 00:24:16,259
YEAH, I REMEMBER THAT.
YEAH.

538
00:24:16,303 --> 00:24:20,002
WELL, UH, WHO DID
THE PHOTOSHOPPING?

539
00:24:20,046 --> 00:24:21,003
I DID, BUT --

540
00:24:21,047 --> 00:24:22,265
YOU DID!

541
00:24:22,309 --> 00:24:23,832
DON'T WORRY.

542
00:24:23,875 --> 00:24:26,530
ALL THE OUT OF POCKET EXPENSE
WILL BE COVERED EVENTUALLY

543
00:24:26,574 --> 00:24:30,273
BY ROYALTIES IN
TWO, THREE YEARS.

544
00:24:30,317 --> 00:24:31,622
FIVE YEARS TOPS.

545
00:24:31,666 --> 00:24:34,321
THAT LONG, HUH?

546
00:24:34,364 --> 00:24:38,238
WELL, I GUESS.

547
00:24:38,281 --> 00:24:40,283
I GUESS I OUGHT TO
BE EXCITED, HUH?

548
00:24:40,327 --> 00:24:42,764
WHY, IT IS VERY EXCITING!

549
00:24:42,807 --> 00:24:44,940
I MEAN, DON'T DOWNPLAY THIS.

550
00:24:44,984 --> 00:24:46,550
YOU'RE A PUBLISHED AUTHOR NOW.

551
00:24:46,594 --> 00:24:47,725
GO OUT AND CELEBRATE.

552
00:24:47,769 --> 00:24:51,294
WELL, THANK YOU.
THANK YOU! [LAUGHS]

553
00:24:51,338 --> 00:24:52,382
HOW ABOUT THAT?

554
00:24:52,426 --> 00:24:53,514
WHERE DO YOU WANT TO GO,
HONEY?

555
00:24:53,557 --> 00:24:54,384
THE SKY IS THE LIMIT.

556
00:24:54,428 --> 00:24:55,429
OH, YOU CHOOSE.

557
00:24:55,472 --> 00:24:57,300
ALRIGHT, WE'LL DO IT.

558
00:24:57,344 --> 00:24:58,693
[LAUGHING]

559
00:24:58,736 --> 00:25:08,790
[HAPPY JAZZY MUSIC]

560
00:25:08,790 --> 00:25:15,753
[HAPPY JAZZY MUSIC]

561
00:25:15,797 --> 00:25:17,668
WE HAD A GREAT TIME.
WE WERE REALLY CELEBRATING.

562
00:25:17,712 --> 00:25:18,887
- AND THAT'S WHY
I DIDN'T GIVE IT --

563
00:25:18,930 --> 00:25:20,454
- I TELL YOU WHAT.

564
00:25:20,497 --> 00:25:22,064
I TRIED TO CALL YOU BUT YOU
DON'T HAVE A GODDAMN PHONE.

565
00:25:22,108 --> 00:25:23,631
YOU UNDERSTAND, DON'T YOU,

566
00:25:23,674 --> 00:25:25,154
THAT'S THE LAST TIME YOU'RE
GOING TO BE USING MY PICKUP.

567
00:25:25,198 --> 00:25:27,374
YOU LEFT ME IN
AN IMPOSSIBLE SITUATION.

568
00:25:27,417 --> 00:25:29,811
I WAS COUNTING ON
USING THAT TRUCK.

569
00:25:29,854 --> 00:25:32,596
WELL. I'M NOT SORRY
YOU FEEL THAT WAY.

570
00:25:32,640 --> 00:25:34,598
THAT'S A LITTLE HARSH.
COME ON.

571
00:25:34,642 --> 00:25:36,165
LET'S LET HIM ENJOY
HIS SUCCESS.

572
00:25:38,124 --> 00:25:39,342
ROSS!
THANKS FOR COMING!

573
00:25:39,386 --> 00:25:40,474
MY PLEASURE.

574
00:25:40,517 --> 00:25:41,649
GREAT TO SEE YOU!

575
00:25:41,692 --> 00:25:42,954
SORRY WE DIDN'T GET
A CHANCE TO TALK.

576
00:25:42,998 --> 00:25:44,173
YOU TAKE CARE.

577
00:25:44,217 --> 00:25:47,089
GODDAMN WEATHER.
CLOUDING OVER. I HATE IT.

578
00:25:49,787 --> 00:25:51,224
YEAH, I BETTER MAKE
A FEW ROUNDS HERE.

579
00:25:51,267 --> 00:25:52,181
OH, SURE.

580
00:25:52,225 --> 00:25:52,921
CATCH UP WITH
YOU IN A MINUTE.

581
00:25:52,964 --> 00:25:53,748
TAKING OFF?

582
00:25:53,791 --> 00:25:54,575
YEP, IT'S A PLEASURE NOW.

583
00:25:54,618 --> 00:25:56,707
GOOD TO SEE YOU, MY FRIEND.

584
00:25:56,751 --> 00:25:57,621
HEY, BRITT!

585
00:25:57,665 --> 00:26:00,059
GIVE ME A RIDE HOME, WILL YOU?

586
00:26:00,102 --> 00:26:01,103
ASSHOLE.

587
00:26:01,147 --> 00:26:04,193
[LAUGHING]

588
00:26:09,416 --> 00:26:10,591
IT'S A LONG WAY.

589
00:26:10,634 --> 00:26:12,680
MAYBE HE'S JUST,
HE DON'T WANT TO BE ALONE.

590
00:26:12,723 --> 00:26:14,377
MAYBE HE'S CONCERNED
THE BOAT WILL GO DOWN

591
00:26:14,421 --> 00:26:16,597
AND EVERYBODY WILL
FORGET ABOUT HIM.

592
00:26:16,640 --> 00:26:20,122
MAYBE HE DOESN'T HAVE ANY
SELF-CONFIDENCE ABOUT MAKING IT.

593
00:26:20,166 --> 00:26:21,689
WELL, HOW LONG HAS HE BEEN
SAILING, FOR PETE'S SAKE?

594
00:26:21,732 --> 00:26:23,560
WELL, WHAT'D HE SAY TO YOU?
WHEN YOU ASKED HIM?

595
00:26:23,604 --> 00:26:24,953
WELL, HE DIDN'T SAY A WHOLE LOT.

596
00:26:24,996 --> 00:26:26,520
DID HE SAY ANYTHING?

597
00:26:26,563 --> 00:26:28,217
WE SAID WE DIDN'T UNDERSTAND
AND HE KEPT GOING ON AND ON,

598
00:26:28,261 --> 00:26:30,741
BABBLING ABOUT HE'S HAVING
SECOND THOUGHTS.

599
00:26:30,785 --> 00:26:31,786
SECOND THOUGHTS.

600
00:26:31,829 --> 00:26:32,787
FINALLY, HE SAID,
"I'M NOT GOING."

601
00:26:32,830 --> 00:26:34,049
HE'S NOT GOING.

602
00:26:34,093 --> 00:26:35,703
SO THAT WAS FINAL,
YOU KNOW, AND, AND --

603
00:26:35,746 --> 00:26:38,184
SHE NEVER SAID ANYTHING
REALLY ABOUT YOU.

604
00:26:38,227 --> 00:26:40,664
SHE JUST SAID, DID I KNOW
HOW TO GET IN TOUCH WITH YOU

605
00:26:40,708 --> 00:26:42,492
AND DID I THINK YOU GUYS

606
00:26:42,536 --> 00:26:45,365
WOULD BE INTERESTED
IN GETTING TOGETHER?

607
00:26:45,408 --> 00:26:46,714
AND I SAID, "YEAH!"

608
00:26:46,757 --> 00:26:47,932
I THOUGHT YOU WOULD BE.

609
00:26:47,976 --> 00:26:49,412
SO IT'S SET UP.

610
00:26:49,456 --> 00:26:50,718
I GOT YOU GETTING TOGETHER
FOR DRINKS TOMORROW NIGHT.

611
00:26:50,761 --> 00:26:52,023
OH, NO.

612
00:26:52,067 --> 00:26:54,417
YEAH. HEY, I TOLD HER
YOU DIDN'T HAVE A PHONE

613
00:26:54,461 --> 00:26:57,116
BUT I'D BE HAPPY
TO TAKE YOU A MESSAGE.

614
00:26:57,159 --> 00:26:58,291
I WISH YOU HADN'T DONE THAT.

615
00:26:58,334 --> 00:27:02,208
YOU KNOW, I REALLY
DON'T WANT TO SEE HER.

616
00:27:02,251 --> 00:27:07,343
WE HAD A GOOD TIME
AT THE PARTY BUT UH, YOU KNOW,

617
00:27:07,387 --> 00:27:12,043
I REALLY TOLD HER
SOME THINGS THAT PROBABLY --

618
00:27:12,087 --> 00:27:13,393
STRETCHED THE TRUTH A LITTLE?

619
00:27:13,436 --> 00:27:15,569
WELL, WHEN SHE REALLY FINDS OUT

620
00:27:15,612 --> 00:27:18,180
ABOUT WHO I AM
AND STUFF LIKE THAT.

621
00:27:18,224 --> 00:27:21,314
THAT THING'LL GO LIKE THAT.

622
00:27:21,357 --> 00:27:22,837
DOESN'T MATTER.
IT WAS A PARTY.

623
00:27:22,880 --> 00:27:24,447
IT WAS JUST SMALL TALK.

624
00:27:24,491 --> 00:27:28,538
BESIDES, YOU GOT OVERNIGHT
TO GET USED TO THE IDEA.

625
00:27:28,582 --> 00:27:30,105
I SET YOU GUYS UP FOR DRINKS.

626
00:27:30,149 --> 00:27:31,759
- NO.
- I GOT IT ALL SET UP.

627
00:27:31,802 --> 00:27:32,890
- NO!
- YUP.

628
00:27:32,934 --> 00:27:34,327
- NO, IT, NOT GONNA --
- SURE IT IS.

629
00:27:34,370 --> 00:27:35,632
IT'S NOT GONNA WORK.

630
00:27:35,676 --> 00:27:37,504
JUST THINK
ABOUT IT OVERNIGHT.

631
00:27:37,547 --> 00:27:39,636
[MOTOR CHUGGING]

632
00:27:39,680 --> 00:27:41,899
YOU KNOW, DAVE, I BROUGHT
MY MANUSCRIPT ALONG AND I --

633
00:27:41,943 --> 00:27:43,466
OH, REALLY?

634
00:27:43,510 --> 00:27:44,815
-- THE OTHER DAY YOU WANTED
TO READ IT AND I SAID, "NO",

635
00:27:44,859 --> 00:27:46,861
BUT I'VE CHANGED MY MIND.

636
00:27:46,904 --> 00:27:47,905
OH, NO KIDDING.

637
00:27:47,949 --> 00:27:49,559
AND UH, YEAH.

638
00:27:49,603 --> 00:27:50,691
I WAS WONDERING WHAT YOU WERE
CARRYING AROUND IN THAT PURSE.

639
00:27:50,734 --> 00:27:51,692
WELL, YOU KNOW,
I'VE BEEN, I'VE BEEN --

640
00:27:51,735 --> 00:27:52,954
[LAUGHTER]

641
00:27:52,997 --> 00:27:55,217
THAT'S NOT A PURSE,
YOU BASTARD.

642
00:27:55,261 --> 00:27:57,263
[LAUGHTER]

643
00:27:57,306 --> 00:27:58,525
THIS IS MY SATCHEL.

644
00:27:58,568 --> 00:27:59,613
WELL, IT'S SO CUTE.

645
00:27:59,656 --> 00:28:01,702
YEAH.
SURE IT IS.

646
00:28:01,745 --> 00:28:04,400
WELL NO, THAT'S GREAT.
I'M HAPPY TO DO IT. SERIOUSLY.

647
00:28:04,444 --> 00:28:07,447
YEAH, I'M NOT JOKING NOW,
THIS IS SERIOUS STUFF BECAUSE --

648
00:28:07,490 --> 00:28:08,535
NO, I UNDERSTAND.

649
00:28:08,578 --> 00:28:10,145
YOU KNOW, THIS IS MY LIFE IN
HERE.

650
00:28:10,189 --> 00:28:13,235
AND SO I'D REALLY APPRECIATE IT
IF YOU'D TAKE A LOOK AT IT.

651
00:28:13,279 --> 00:28:14,105
SURE.

652
00:28:14,149 --> 00:28:14,715
I WANT YOU TO BE CRITICAL.

653
00:28:14,758 --> 00:28:15,803
OKAY.

654
00:28:15,846 --> 00:28:17,326
I WANT YOU TO
REALLY UH, YOU KNOW,

655
00:28:17,370 --> 00:28:19,415
GIVE IT YOUR ALL IF YOU WOULD

656
00:28:19,459 --> 00:28:23,506
AND BE VERY HONEST
ABOUT WHAT YOU THINK OF IT.

657
00:28:23,550 --> 00:28:26,161
"SKIRTING THE EDGE."

658
00:28:26,205 --> 00:28:29,208
I LIKE THAT TITLE.

659
00:28:29,251 --> 00:28:30,296
STORY OF MY LIFE.

660
00:28:32,472 --> 00:28:34,300
I'LL BE HAPPY TO READ IT.

661
00:28:34,343 --> 00:28:35,953
THANK YOU.

662
00:28:39,827 --> 00:28:46,268
[MUSIC]

663
00:28:46,312 --> 00:28:48,270
I TOOK FLORENCE
COYOTE HUNTING EVERY DAY

664
00:28:48,314 --> 00:28:50,533
BECAUSE THAT ACTIVITY
INVOLVED WALKING MANY MILES

665
00:28:50,577 --> 00:28:52,753
ACROSS THE KANSAS PRAIRIE

666
00:28:52,796 --> 00:28:54,842
AND I WAS HOPING TO WEAR
HER OUT TO AN EARLY BED

667
00:28:54,885 --> 00:29:00,195
SO THAT I COULD JOIN
MY OTHER GIRLFRIEND, FRANCES.

668
00:29:00,239 --> 00:29:01,849
THE TORRID AFFAIR
I HAD WITH FRANCES

669
00:29:01,892 --> 00:29:03,938
WAS ALSO DOOMED TO FAILURE.

670
00:29:03,981 --> 00:29:07,768
SOMEHOW, I KNEW THAT ONE BUILT
ON SEX ALONE COULD NOT LAST.

671
00:29:07,811 --> 00:29:09,291
DESPITE HER DEVOTION,

672
00:29:09,335 --> 00:29:12,642
I ALSO INTUITIVELY KNEW
IF I DIDN'T LEAVE HER SOON,

673
00:29:12,686 --> 00:29:13,904
WE WOULD MARRY
AND THAT WOULD BE

674
00:29:13,948 --> 00:29:16,298
THE LIFETIME DISASTER
FOR BOTH OF US.

675
00:29:16,342 --> 00:29:18,474
MOST OF MY SEXUAL EXPERIENCES
ARE A BLUR.

676
00:29:18,518 --> 00:29:20,215
THEY ARE COMPLETELY FUZZY.

677
00:29:20,259 --> 00:29:21,608
AFTER I KNOCKED UP HELEN,

678
00:29:21,651 --> 00:29:23,349
I BEGAN TO LOSE COUNT
OF MY PARTNERS.

679
00:29:23,392 --> 00:29:26,613
TODAY, I ESTIMATE SLEEPING
WITH AT LEAST 50 OR 60 WOMEN

680
00:29:26,656 --> 00:29:28,179
