WELL, IT IS NICE BUT
IT'S ALSO NICE TO BE TOGETHER.

1572
01:10:27,854 --> 01:10:32,380
MY SON, BEN.
MY DAUGHTER, TESS.

1573
01:10:32,424 --> 01:10:38,169
AND MY HUSBAND.
HE DIED 11 YEARS AGO.

1574
01:10:38,212 --> 01:10:46,438
HE WAS QUITE SICK
BUT I TOOK CARE OF HIM.

1575
01:10:46,481 --> 01:10:49,093
I BET THAT WAS
EXHAUSTING, HUH?

1576
01:10:49,136 --> 01:10:54,011
WELL, YES.
BUT THAT'S JUST WHAT YOU DO.

1577
01:10:54,054 --> 01:11:00,147
HAVE YOU NOT EVER
HAD SOMEONE SPECIAL?

1578
01:11:00,191 --> 01:11:03,411
WELL, NOT, NOT THAT
KIND OF SPECIAL.

1579
01:11:03,455 --> 01:11:07,241
I'VE HAD PEOPLE.
I MEAN, I'VE HAD RELATIONSHIPS.

1580
01:11:07,285 --> 01:11:12,986
YEARS AGO I HAD A YOUNG LADY
THAT WE WERE PRETTY CLOSE.

1581
01:11:13,030 --> 01:11:16,250
I USED TO TAKE HER SAILING
ALL THE TIME ON MY DAD'S BOAT.

1582
01:11:16,294 --> 01:11:19,210
WELL, IT WAS MY DAD'S BOAT
AT THAT TIME.

1583
01:11:19,253 --> 01:11:21,995
AND LATER ON, HE GAVE ME
THE BOAT AND UH,

1584
01:11:22,039 --> 01:11:23,301
I NEEDED A PLACE TO LIVE

1585
01:11:23,344 --> 01:11:25,651
AND IT HAD SOME
SENTIMENTAL VALUE TO ME, TOO,

1586
01:11:25,694 --> 01:11:31,831
AT THE TIME SO,
THAT'S WHY I HAVE THE BOAT.

1587
01:11:31,875 --> 01:11:37,228
YOU'VE NEVER
THOUGHT ABOUT MOVING?

1588
01:11:37,271 --> 01:11:38,882
YEAH, I'VE THOUGHT ABOUT MOVING.

1589
01:11:38,925 --> 01:11:42,363
I MEAN, IT'S, THAT'S ALWAYS AN
OPTION BUT ON THE OTHER HAND,

1590
01:11:42,407 --> 01:11:46,541
I'M PRETTY COMFORTABLE
ON THE BOAT.

1591
01:12:03,210 --> 01:12:07,388
WHAT DO YOU THINK
YOU DID TO YOUR BACK?

1592
01:12:07,432 --> 01:12:09,521
WELL, I'M NOT, NOT SURE.

1593
01:12:09,564 --> 01:12:12,785
IT MIGHT HAVE BEEN THE WAY
I SLEPT OR SOMETHING.

1594
01:12:12,829 --> 01:12:15,005
OH, I THINK YOU
NEED A REAL BED.

1595
01:12:15,048 --> 01:12:19,139
NOT THAT OLD COT ON
THAT OLD BOAT OF YOURS.

1596
01:12:19,183 --> 01:12:21,185
I THINK I FEEL A LOT
BETTER RIGHT NOW.

1597
01:12:21,228 --> 01:12:22,751
WELL, YOU KNOW, THE MANUAL SAID

1598
01:12:22,795 --> 01:12:25,929
I COULD USE THIS FOR
15 CONTINUOUS MINUTES.

1599
01:12:25,972 --> 01:12:27,147
I THINK THAT'S --

1600
01:12:27,191 --> 01:12:28,670
OH, I DON'T THINK
WE HAVE TO GO THAT LONG.

1601
01:12:28,714 --> 01:12:31,108
I THINK I'M FULLY RECOVERED NOW.

1602
01:12:31,151 --> 01:12:32,500
WELL, ARE YOU SURE?

1603
01:12:32,544 --> 01:12:35,155
BECAUSE I HAVEN'T EVEN DONE
YOUR LOWER BACK YET.

1604
01:12:35,199 --> 01:12:36,026
OH GOD.

1605
01:12:38,811 --> 01:12:40,987
- THANK YOU.
- SURE.

1606
01:12:47,907 --> 01:12:51,955
BRITT?

1607
01:12:51,998 --> 01:12:54,914
I THINK YOU SHOULD
SELL YOUR BOAT.

1608
01:12:54,958 --> 01:12:57,090
SELL MY BOAT?

1609
01:12:57,134 --> 01:12:58,744
I'VE BEEN GIVING IT
SOME THOUGHT.

1610
01:12:58,787 --> 01:13:03,880
AND I FEEL VERY
COMFORTABLE WITH YOU.

1611
01:13:03,923 --> 01:13:06,534
SELL MY BOAT.
HMM.

1612
01:13:06,578 --> 01:13:12,366
SURE.
YOU CAN COME STAY WITH ME.

1613
01:13:12,410 --> 01:13:15,935
I'M HUMBLED THAT
YOU'VE ASKED ME.

1614
01:13:15,979 --> 01:13:21,201
AND THIS, UH,
THIS IS A BIG THING WITH ME,

1615
01:13:21,245 --> 01:13:27,512
THIS THING WITH YOU
AND THERE'S A LOT GO --

1616
01:13:27,555 --> 01:13:28,905
WE COULD START TOMORROW.

1617
01:13:28,948 --> 01:13:30,167
WE COULD GET AN EARLY START,

1618
01:13:30,210 --> 01:13:34,606
GET UP EARLY AND
I COULD RENT A U-HAUL.

1619
01:13:34,649 --> 01:13:37,000
YOU COULD DRIVE IT.
I DON'T THINK I COULD DRIVE IT.

1620
01:13:37,043 --> 01:13:38,697
BUT YOU COULD DRIVE
THE U-HAUL.

1621
01:13:38,740 --> 01:13:41,221
WE WOULD JUST BACK IT
RIGHT UP TO YOUR BOAT.

1622
01:13:41,265 --> 01:13:44,224
I THINK WE COULD GET EVERYTHING
IN ONE LOAD AND WE'D BE DONE.

1623
01:13:44,268 --> 01:13:47,314
WELL, I CAN'T DO IT TOMORROW.

1624
01:13:47,358 --> 01:13:49,273
WHY?
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

1625
01:13:54,843 --> 01:14:08,031
[DUCK CALL QUACKING BADLY]

1626
01:14:08,074 --> 01:14:10,598
[COUGHING]

1627
01:14:10,642 --> 01:14:12,209
YOU KNOW, DAVE,
I GOTTA TELL YOU,

1628
01:14:12,252 --> 01:14:14,385
YOU'RE NOT GOING TO SEE
MUCH THROUGH THOSE BINOCULARS.

1629
01:14:14,428 --> 01:14:15,560
I KNOW.

1630
01:14:15,603 --> 01:14:19,085
YOU KNOW,
THEY'RE KIND OF SUPERFLUOUS

1631
01:14:19,129 --> 01:14:20,260
TO OUR PURPOSE HERE.

1632
01:14:20,304 --> 01:14:22,088
YEAH, PRETTY NARROW
FIELD OF VIEW.

1633
01:14:22,132 --> 01:14:27,050
I THINK I'M BETTER OFF
WITHOUT THEM ALMOST.

1634
01:14:27,093 --> 01:14:32,055
[MUSIC]

1635
01:14:32,098 --> 01:14:33,534
BOY! IT'S COLD OUT HERE.

1636
01:14:33,578 --> 01:14:35,536
IT IS COLD, GODDAMMIT!

1637
01:14:35,580 --> 01:14:39,236
GONNA HAVE A LITTLE
WARM-UP HERE.

1638
01:14:39,279 --> 01:14:41,238
- OH!
- HEY, DAVE.

1639
01:14:41,281 --> 01:14:43,849
I'M SORRY.
THAT'S NOT ALLOWED.

1640
01:14:43,892 --> 01:14:46,939
I SHOULD HAVE TOLD YOU
BEFORE BUT WE DON'T,

1641
01:14:46,983 --> 01:14:49,376
WE DON'T DRINK
WHEN WE'RE HUNTING.

1642
01:14:49,420 --> 01:14:50,464
IT'S OKAY AFTERWARDS.

1643
01:14:50,508 --> 01:14:52,075
YOU CAN GET SHITFACED
IF YOU WANT.

1644
01:14:52,118 --> 01:14:53,728
YOU KNOW WHAT?

1645
01:14:53,772 --> 01:14:55,208
THERE'S MORE DUCKS AROUND MY
BOAT THAN THERE ARE AROUND HERE.

1646
01:14:55,252 --> 01:14:57,384
WE COULD GET TO CLUB THEM
IN THE HEAD.

1647
01:14:57,428 --> 01:14:59,865
I TOLD YOU IT'D BE TOUGH.
JUST, YOU KNOW.

1648
01:14:59,908 --> 01:15:02,041
I DON'T THINK WE'VE SEEN A DUCK
SINCE WE GOT OUT HERE.

1649
01:15:02,085 --> 01:15:05,218
I DON'T THINK THIS
IS A GOOD IDEA.

1650
01:15:05,262 --> 01:15:09,396
I DON'T THINK THOSE DECOYS
ARE ARRANGED RIGHT, EITHER.

1651
01:15:09,440 --> 01:15:12,269
I GOT SOME QUESTION
ABOUT THAT, TOO.

1652
01:15:12,312 --> 01:15:14,358
YOU REALIZE HOW RIDICULOUS
THAT WOULD LOOK

1653
01:15:14,401 --> 01:15:16,012
IF YOU WERE TO FLY OVER THEM?

1654
01:15:16,055 --> 01:15:18,057
HOW A DUCK WOULD LOOK DOWN
ON THOSE THINGS?

1655
01:15:18,101 --> 01:15:19,798
YOU GUYS DON'T KNOW
WHAT YOU'RE TALKING ABOUT.

1656
01:15:19,841 --> 01:15:20,842
HUH?

1657
01:15:20,886 --> 01:15:21,800
THE DECOYS ARE FINE.

1658
01:15:21,843 --> 01:15:22,757
OH NO.
I DON'T KNOW.

1659
01:15:22,801 --> 01:15:24,194
THERE ARE NO DAMN DUCKS.

1660
01:15:24,237 --> 01:15:25,456
WELL, I THINK THEY ARE
A TREMENDOUS WASTE OF TIME.

1661
01:15:25,499 --> 01:15:27,066
WELL, I TOLD YOU THAT BEFORE.

1662
01:15:27,110 --> 01:15:29,460
THE ONLY DUCKS I'VE SEEN AROUND
HERE ARE THOSE DAMN DECOYS.

1663
01:15:29,503 --> 01:15:30,722
WHERE ARE MY GODDAMN WADERS?

1664
01:15:30,765 --> 01:15:34,769
WHY DON'T WE JUST GET
A CHICKEN AT COSTCO?

1665
01:15:34,813 --> 01:15:37,816
MIGHTY DUCK HUNTER YOU ARE,
FOR CHRIST SAKES.

1666
01:15:37,859 --> 01:15:43,387
[MUSIC]

1667
01:15:43,430 --> 01:15:45,258
HEY, YOU BEEN LAID YET?

1668
01:15:45,302 --> 01:15:47,608
THAT'S NONE OF YOUR BUSINESS.

1669
01:15:47,652 --> 01:15:50,481
I'M REALLY PROUD OF YOU, BRITT,
FOR CHANGING YOUR LIFESTYLE.

1670
01:15:50,524 --> 01:15:52,178
YOU KNOW,
I THOUGHT YOU WAS STUCK

1671
01:15:52,222 --> 01:15:54,006
AND GONNA BE AN
ASSHOLE ALL YOUR LIFE

1672
01:15:54,050 --> 01:15:56,313
AND BY GOLLY, YOU KNOW,
YOU'VE REALLY COME 'ROUND.

1673
01:15:56,356 --> 01:15:57,836
I'VE SEEN YOU WITH
YOUR GIRLFRIEND

1674
01:15:57,879 --> 01:15:59,098
AND YOU LOOK REALLY GOOD.

1675
01:15:59,142 --> 01:16:01,013
AND YOU'RE GOOD FOR HER.

1676
01:16:01,057 --> 01:16:03,059
YOU KNOW,
YOU'RE DOING FINE.

1677
01:16:03,102 --> 01:16:05,452
I'M PROUD OF YOU.
I REALLY AM.

1678
01:16:05,496 --> 01:16:07,324
- YOU THINK SO?
- YEAH!

1679
01:16:07,367 --> 01:16:16,028
[MUSIC]

1680
01:16:16,072 --> 01:16:19,336
SO, YOU'RE BACK
ON SENIOR CONNECTIONS?

1681
01:16:19,379 --> 01:16:22,904
NO, NO. NO, I'M NOT GOING
TO DO THAT.

1682
01:16:22,948 --> 01:16:26,299
I'M DONE WITH THAT.

1683
01:16:26,343 --> 01:16:29,085
WELL, WHERE ARE YOU
GOING TO NEXT, THEN?

1684
01:16:29,128 --> 01:16:31,783
DAVE! DAVE!
YOU'RE NOT DOING ANY GOOD.

1685
01:16:31,826 --> 01:16:34,307
COME ON, GET OUT OF
THE GODDAMN WATER.

1686
01:16:34,351 --> 01:16:43,055
AHH! AHH!

1687
01:16:43,099 --> 01:16:45,536
YOU GOING TO LET ME
READ THAT BOOK?

1688
01:16:45,579 --> 01:16:47,190
NO.

1689
01:16:49,583 --> 01:16:50,802
WHY NOT?

1690
01:16:50,845 --> 01:16:53,674
I'M KIND OF LOOKING
FORWARD TO SEEING UH --

1691
01:16:53,718 --> 01:16:55,633
ARE YOU SICK OR SOMETHING?

1692
01:16:55,676 --> 01:16:57,113
ARE YOU COMING DOWN WITH...?

1693
01:16:57,156 --> 01:17:00,507
I DON'T KNOW. IT'S COLD, MAN!
MY FEET ARE FREEZING.

1694
01:17:05,556 --> 01:17:10,300
OH!

1695
01:17:10,343 --> 01:17:13,955
[SNIFFING]

1696
01:17:13,999 --> 01:17:17,089
[WHEEZY COUGHING]

1697
01:17:27,491 --> 01:17:29,232
[BANG!]

1698
01:17:30,972 --> 01:17:31,712
OHH.

1699
01:17:39,416 --> 01:17:52,385
[COUNTRY MUSIC]
[COUGHING CONTINUES]

1700
01:17:52,429 --> 01:17:57,956
[MUSIC CONTINUES]

1701
01:17:57,956 --> 01:18:02,439
[MUSIC CONTINUES]

1702
01:18:20,283 --> 01:18:23,895
I KNOW WE POSSESS POWERFUL TOOLS FOR OUR SURVIVAL

1703
01:18:23,938 --> 01:18:27,290
BUT FEW OF US REALIZE
OUR VERY OWN POTENTIAL.

1704
01:18:27,333 --> 01:18:32,338
AND THIS I BELIEVE, A GOOD LIFE IS ONE OF RISKS COUPLED WITH,

1705
01:18:32,382 --> 01:18:34,471
WELL OF COURSE,
CREATIVITY, LOVE,

1706
01:18:34,514 --> 01:18:38,953
AND GIVING BACK WITHIN
ONE'S CAPACITY TO DO SO.

1707
01:18:38,997 --> 01:18:40,390
THE SINGLE MOST IMPORTANT REGRET

1708
01:18:40,433 --> 01:18:42,696
IS THAT I DIDN'T LIVE UP
TO THAT CODE.

1709
01:18:42,740 --> 01:18:47,266
YET, MY LIFE HAS BEEN
EXCEEDINGLY FULL AND BOUNTIFUL

1710
01:18:47,310 --> 01:18:50,574
AND THAT HELPS ME KEEP
TILTING TOWARDS WINDMILLS,

1711
01:18:50,617 --> 01:18:53,707
ALL OF WHICH REMINDS ME
OF A LANGSTON HUGHES POEM.

1712
01:18:53,751 --> 01:18:56,536
IT'S ONE OF MY FAVORITES.

1713
01:18:56,580 --> 01:18:59,322
'TWO MEN LOOKED UP
FROM THE PRISON BARS,

1714
01:18:59,365 --> 01:19:03,282
ONE SAW MUD
AND ONE SAW STARS.'

1715
01:19:03,326 --> 01:19:05,502
IF I LEARNED ANYTHING
OVER THESE MANY YEARS,

1716
01:19:05,545 --> 01:19:08,679
IT IS THAT THE THRILL OF MY LIFE HAS BEEN MORE IN THE CHASE

1717
01:19:08,722 --> 01:19:10,507
AND NOT SO MUCH IN THE CATCHING.

1718
01:19:10,550 --> 01:19:12,204
I GUESS SOME
THINGS NEVER CHANGE.

1719
01:19:12,248 --> 01:19:15,816
I JUST KEEP GOING
AROUND AND AROUND.

1720
01:19:15,860 --> 01:19:18,645
THAT WHICH WE ARE, WE ARE.

1721
01:19:18,689 --> 01:19:21,169
COUGH! EXCUSE ME.

1722
01:19:21,213 --> 01:19:25,783
SO, AT SOME POINT THIS
RAMBLING NARRATIVE MUST END.

1723
01:19:25,826 --> 01:19:27,132
AND I'VE ALWAYS BEEN ONE

1724
01:19:27,175 --> 01:19:29,613
WHO WOULD RATHER JUMP
BEFORE I'M PUSHED.

1725
01:19:29,656 --> 01:19:33,312
SO FOR ME, IT'S SOONER
RATHER THAN LATER.

1726
01:19:33,356 --> 01:19:35,009
SO BE IT.

1727
01:19:35,053 --> 01:19:45,106
[CHEERS] [APPLAUSE]
YAY!

1728
01:19:45,106 --> 01:19:51,461
[CHEERS] [APPLAUSE]
YAY!

1729
01:19:56,988 --> 01:19:59,338
OH, I CAN'T BELIEVE
THOSE AIRLINES

1730
01:19:59,382 --> 01:20:04,865
CHARGE $20 FOR EXTRA BAGGAGE.

1731
01:20:04,909 --> 01:20:07,694
UH-HUH.
YOU NEED SOME HELP?

1732
01:20:07,738 --> 01:20:10,218
OH. THAT'D BE GREAT.
THANKS.

1733
01:20:13,526 --> 01:20:15,398
OH, YEAH.

1734
01:20:15,441 --> 01:20:19,315
LET'S GET THAT
CENTERED A LITTLE BIT.

1735
01:20:19,358 --> 01:20:20,838
OH, SUPER.

1736
01:20:20,881 --> 01:20:21,882
THERE YOU GO.

1737
01:20:21,926 --> 01:20:22,187
HOW'D YOU DO THAT?

1738
01:20:24,842 --> 01:20:26,104
THANK YOU, KIND SIR.

1739
01:20:26,147 --> 01:20:28,106
YOU'RE WELCOME.

1740
01:20:28,149 --> 01:20:30,891
I THINK THIS IS GOING TO BE FUN.
I'M LOOKING FORWARD TO THE TRIP.

1741
01:20:30,935 --> 01:20:31,936
ARE YOU SERIOUS?

1742
01:20:31,979 --> 01:20:33,024
YEAH?

1743
01:20:33,067 --> 01:20:35,156
OH, I'M REALLY HAPPY.

1744
01:20:35,200 --> 01:20:36,549
THAT'S SO GREAT.
I CAN'T WAIT.

1745
01:20:36,593 --> 01:20:38,899
- IT'LL BE GREAT.
- OH! IT'S WONDERFUL.

1746
01:20:38,943 --> 01:20:40,727
SAY, I JUST HAVE TO GO
TO THE BATHROOM FOR A MINUTE

1747
01:20:40,771 --> 01:20:43,382
'CAUSE I DON'T WANT TO USE THOSE
UGLY LAVATORIES ON THE PLANE.

1748
01:20:43,426 --> 01:20:44,905
OKAY, OKAY.

1749
01:20:44,949 --> 01:20:46,559
HOW MUCH TIME DO WE HAVE?

1750
01:20:46,603 --> 01:20:48,518
OH, 15 OR 20 MINUTES.

1751
01:20:48,561 --> 01:20:50,824
OKAY.

1752
01:20:50,868 --> 01:20:56,395
[SOFT JAZZY MUSIC]

1753
01:20:56,395 --> 01:21:00,878
[SOFT JAZZY MUSIC]

1754
01:21:22,421 --> 01:21:24,118
[BREAKING GLASS]

1755
01:21:31,604 --> 01:21:34,433
WHAT WAS THAT?
DID SOMETHING BREAK?

1756
01:21:34,477 --> 01:21:36,566
OH, I BUMPED THE VASE
WITH THE CLUB.

1757
01:21:36,609 --> 01:21:38,437
NOTHING SERIOUS.

1758
01:21:38,481 --> 01:21:41,571
- OH.
- JUST BROKE IT.

1759
01:21:41,614 --> 01:21:43,399
OKAY.
LET ME GET THE VACUUM.

1760
01:21:43,442 --> 01:21:44,400
OKAY.

1761
01:21:47,272 --> 01:21:48,316
PUT ON SOME SHOES.

1762
01:21:48,360 --> 01:21:49,579
I DON'T WANT YOU
TO CUT YOUR FEET.

1763
01:21:49,622 --> 01:21:50,841
YEAH, THANKS.

1764
01:22:04,898 --> 01:22:06,204
E. COLI IS EVERYWHERE.

1765
01:22:06,247 --> 01:22:07,945
- E. COLI?
- YEAH!

1766
01:22:07,988 --> 01:22:09,686
YOU NOTICE ONLY THE PEOPLE
THAT DIE FROM E. COLI

1767
01:22:09,729 --> 01:22:11,818
ARE KIND OF
SICKLY PEOPLE ANYWAY.

1768
01:22:11,862 --> 01:22:13,516
IF YOU'RE GOOD AND
STRONG AND HEALTHY,

1769
01:22:13,559 --> 01:22:15,474
YOU CAN EAT A RARE HAMBURGER.

1770
01:22:15,518 --> 01:22:17,084
IT'S NOT GOING TO KILL YOU.

1771
01:22:17,128 --> 01:22:19,913
[CHATTER]

1772
01:22:19,957 --> 01:22:21,349
IT'S A MATTER OF LIABILITY

1773
01:22:21,393 --> 01:22:24,309
IF YOU DON'T COOK HAMBURGER
SAFELY FOR THE PUBLIC.

1774
01:22:24,352 --> 01:22:26,877
IT HAS TO BE HEATED TO
AT LEAST 145 DEGREES.

1775
01:22:26,920 --> 01:22:30,446
[CHATTER]

1776
01:22:30,489 --> 01:22:32,230
YOU ONLY BRING GRIFFEY
IN AND YOU LOOK AT IT.

1777
01:22:32,273 --> 01:22:33,797
YOU LOOK AT HOW
MUCH YOU'RE PAYING

1778
01:22:33,840 --> 01:22:36,495
AND YOU LOOK AT HOW MUCH
YOU'RE BRINGING TO THE STANDS --

1779
01:22:48,115 --> 01:22:52,163
HOLY SHIT!...

1780
01:22:52,206 --> 01:22:56,210
OH, SHIT!
I CAN'T SEE A DAMN THING NOW.

1781
01:22:56,254 --> 01:22:58,212
WHERE'S A LIGHT WHEN I NEED ONE.

1782
01:22:58,256 --> 01:22:59,649
[CELL PHONE RINGTONE]

1783
01:22:59,692 --> 01:23:04,871
OH, DAMN TELEPHONE.

1784
01:23:04,915 --> 01:23:08,048
WHO'S THERE?

1785
01:23:08,092 --> 01:23:09,310
GIVE ME A SECOND HERE.

1786
01:23:09,354 --> 01:23:14,446
I WANT TO GET THE
LIGHTS BACK ON.

1787
01:23:14,490 --> 01:23:15,665
[CRASH!]

1788
01:23:15,708 --> 01:23:16,796
OH, HEY!

1789
01:23:16,840 --> 01:23:18,058
I JUST PUT SOME BREAD
IN THE TOASTER

1790
01:23:18,102 --> 01:23:21,148
AND IT SHORTED OUT
AND BLEW THE BREAKER.

1791
01:23:21,192 --> 01:23:24,674
SORRY, I GUESS MY PHONE
WAS ON A VIBRATE.

1792
01:23:24,717 --> 01:23:26,197
GODDAMN IT.

1793
01:23:26,240 --> 01:23:29,809
I WAS MAKING MYSELF
A PIECE OF TOAST.

1794
01:23:29,853 --> 01:23:32,029
WELL, YEAH, THAT'S WHAT I'M
GOING TO HAVE FOR DINNER.

1795
01:23:32,072 --> 01:23:36,947
NO, I'LL PUT SOME, I'LL PUT
SOME BUTTER AND JAM ON IT.

1796
01:23:36,990 --> 01:23:40,124
I THINK -- I KIND OF LIKE THAT.

1797
01:23:40,167 --> 01:23:42,518
BUT, UH, PROBABLY THE LAST
PIECE OF TOAST

1798
01:23:42,561 --> 01:23:47,000
I HAVE TONIGHT BECAUSE
THE TOASTER BROKE.

1799
01:23:47,044 --> 01:23:48,306
WELL, I KNOW I SHOULD
EAT SOMETHING

1800
01:23:48,349 --> 01:23:50,003
A LITTLE BIT BETTER THAN THAT

1801
01:23:50,047 --> 01:23:53,006
BUT I'M TIRED AND I DON'T WANT
TO TAKE A LITTLE TIME TO --

1802
01:23:53,050 --> 01:23:54,268
I UNDERSTAND.

1803
01:23:54,312 --> 01:24:01,058
YEAH...
OH, YOU MEAN TONIGHT?

1804
01:24:01,101 --> 01:24:04,757
WELL.
I'M PRETTY TIRED, YOU KNOW.

1805
01:24:04,801 --> 01:24:06,193
CAN'T WE DO THAT
IN THE MORNING?

1806
01:24:06,237 --> 01:24:09,588
HAVE A CUP OF COFFEE
OR SOMETHING?

1807
01:24:09,632 --> 01:24:14,332
I AM KIND OF TIRED
AND I DON'T SEE WELL AT NIGHT.

1808
01:24:14,375 --> 01:24:19,467
FOR THAT MATTER, I COULD GO
TO SLEEP AND RUN OFF THE ROAD.

1809
01:24:22,209 --> 01:24:26,257
YEAH. YEAH. OKAY.

1810
01:24:26,300 --> 01:24:29,129
WELL, THANK YOU.
GOODNIGHT!

1811
01:24:50,716 --> 01:24:52,588
WELL, I KNOW I'D
SAID I'D BE EARLY.

1812
01:24:52,631 --> 01:24:55,025
AND I KNOW I TOLD YOU
I'M AN EARLY RISER

1813
01:24:55,068 --> 01:24:58,768
BUT I NEEDED SOME
MORE SLEEP, I GUESS.

1814
01:24:58,811 --> 01:25:00,378
WELL, LISTEN, I GOT SOME --

1815
01:25:00,421 --> 01:25:02,859
WHY DON'T I PACK A FEW BOXES
AND PUT THEM IN MY PICKUP

1816
01:25:02,902 --> 01:25:05,209
AND WHEN I COME OVER

1817
01:25:05,252 --> 01:25:10,301
WE'LL AT LEAST HAVE SOME
OF THAT STUFF TAKEN CARE OF.

1818
01:25:10,344 --> 01:25:14,261
WELL -- [GRUNTS] -- WHY
DON'T I DO THAT ANYWAY?

1819
01:25:14,305 --> 01:25:17,700
OKAY? I KNOW THAT WE'LL
GET OUR DAYS GOING

1820
01:25:17,743 --> 01:25:20,833
JUST A LITTLE LATER BUT WE'LL,

1821
01:25:20,877 --> 01:25:24,924
WE'LL MOVE REAL FAST,
I PROMISE.

1822
01:25:24,968 --> 01:25:30,669
YEAH. YEAH. YEAH. I, YEAH,
I HAD A GOOD NIGHT'S SLEEP.

1823
01:25:30,713 --> 01:25:33,977
YES.
I LIKE SLEEPING HERE.

1824
01:25:34,020 --> 01:25:35,935
WELL, I LIKE SLEEPING
AT YOUR PLACE, TOO.

1825
01:25:35,979 --> 01:25:40,723
BUT THIS, I MEAN, NO,
OLD HABITS...

1826
01:25:40,766 --> 01:25:46,685
ALRIGHT. WELL.
SORRY I'M SO LATE. BYE.

1827
01:25:55,781 --> 01:25:57,174
SHIT.

1828
01:26:30,990 --> 01:26:32,557
[BLEEP!]

1829
01:26:44,482 --> 01:26:47,659
HELLO, FROM PALM SPRINGS
WHERE I'M THE PROUD NEW OWNER

1830
01:26:47,703 --> 01:26:50,401
OF A CONDO IN THE
COMMUNITY OF IRONWOOD.

1831
01:26:50,444 --> 01:26:52,446
I'VE ATTACHED SOME PHOTOS.

1832
01:26:52,490 --> 01:26:54,797
CHRIS HAS BEEN WORKING
ON THE INTERIOR DESIGN

1833
01:26:54,840 --> 01:26:58,757
WHILE I HIT THE GOLF COURSE
WITH MY FRIEND, DOUG CARLSON.

1834
01:26:58,801 --> 01:27:00,759
IT'S NOT BAD HERE AT ALL.

1835
01:27:00,803 --> 01:27:02,152
THE WEATHER IS VERY PLEASANT

1836
01:27:02,195 --> 01:27:03,806
AND THERE ARE LOTS
OF SOCIAL GATHERINGS

1837
01:27:03,849 --> 01:27:06,765
AND EVENTS THAT KEEP US BUSY.

1838
01:27:06,809 --> 01:27:08,288
WE'VE JUST MET SOME
WONDERFUL PEOPLE HERE

1839
01:27:08,332 --> 01:27:11,117
FROM ALL OVER THE COUNTRY.

1840
01:27:11,161 --> 01:27:14,120
WE DECIDED NOT TO TAKE
THE BAJA CRUISE THIS YEAR.

1841
01:27:14,164 --> 01:27:16,775
CHRIS HAS DECIDED WE'RE
GOING TO PARIS INSTEAD.

1842
01:27:16,819 --> 01:27:18,603
SO I'M NOT SURE
WHEN I'LL BE HOME.

1843
01:27:18,646 --> 01:27:21,432
PROBABLY SOMETIME IN THE SUMMER.

1844
01:27:21,475 --> 01:27:23,782
UNTIL THEN, KEEP DRY UP THERE.

1845
01:27:23,826 --> 01:27:25,305
YOU'RE BUD, DAVE.

1846
01:27:28,700 --> 01:27:33,966
[MUSIC]

1847
01:27:33,966 --> 01:27:38,710
[MUSIC]

1848
01:29:27,906 --> 01:29:31,040
[HONK! HONK! HONK!]

1849
01:29:31,083 --> 01:29:34,957
[LONG HORN BLAST]

1850
01:29:35,000 --> 01:29:37,916
[HONK-HONK-HONK! HONK! HONK!]

1851
01:29:37,960 --> 01:29:42,355
[HO-O-O-O-O-ONK!]

1852
01:29:45,881 --> 01:29:48,318
OH, JESUS CHRIST!

1853
01:29:52,278 --> 01:29:54,672
[BANG! BANG! BANG! BANG!]

1854
01:29:59,895 --> 01:30:01,418
HEY, BOB!

1855
01:30:04,203 --> 01:30:14,257
[TV AUDIO]

1856
01:30:14,257 --> 01:30:27,531
[TV AUDIO]

1857
01:30:27,574 --> 01:30:34,494
HEY, BOB! BOB!

1858
01:30:34,538 --> 01:30:37,323
OH, HI!
DON'T YOU EVER KNOCK!

1859
01:30:42,546 --> 01:30:45,070
I KNOCKED SEVERAL TIMES
OUT THERE.

1860
01:30:45,114 --> 01:30:47,290
I THOUGHT YOU WERE
SUPPOSED TO BE SICK!

1861
01:30:47,333 --> 01:30:49,727
OH, I'M FEELING,
I'M FEELING BETTER.

1862
01:30:49,770 --> 01:30:53,992
I UH, DO WANT THE DOCTOR
TO LOOK AT MY KNEE THOUGH

1863
01:30:54,036 --> 01:30:56,386
BECAUSE IT'S BEEN
GIVING ME FITS.

1864
01:30:58,779 --> 01:31:00,477
GET READY THEN.

1865
01:31:00,520 --> 01:31:02,174
HELL, I WAS BORN READY.

1866
01:31:08,006 --> 01:31:09,790
WELL, IT'S A LADY
FROM THE CHOIR.

1867
01:31:09,834 --> 01:31:12,097
SHE'S NEW IN THE CHOIR AND UM --

1868
01:31:12,141 --> 01:31:13,925
- REALLY?
- YEAH.

1869
01:31:13,969 --> 01:31:16,623
I, YOU KNOW, IT JUST SEEMED
AN AUTOMATIC THING.

1870
01:31:16,667 --> 01:31:19,583
WE KIND OF GRAVITATED TOGETHER.

1871
01:31:19,626 --> 01:31:23,979
UNLIKE CAROLYN, SHE'S OUT-GOING
AND CAN TALK AND SHE CAN DANCE.

1872
01:31:24,022 --> 01:31:26,503
SHE, UH, SHE'S TEACHING ME
TO DANCE THE SALSA.

1873
01:31:26,546 --> 01:31:29,027
NO! YOU SOUND LIKE
YOU'RE IN LOVE AGAIN.

1874
01:31:29,071 --> 01:31:31,334
NO, NO, NO, NO, NO.
IT'S NOT THAT.

1875
01:31:31,377 --> 01:31:32,683
WELL, I DON'T KNOW.

1876
01:31:32,726 --> 01:31:35,294
WELL, SHE TAUGHT ME
THIS PHRASE 'MUY CALIENTE'

1877
01:31:35,338 --> 01:31:37,166
WHICH MEANS HOTTER THAN HELL.
[CHUCKLES]

1878
01:31:37,209 --> 01:31:39,124
MAYBE THAT'S JUST A LITTLE BIT
TOO MUCH EXCITEMENT

1879
01:31:39,168 --> 01:31:41,431
FOR A MAN OF YOUR SENIORITY.

1880
01:31:41,474 --> 01:31:44,651
HEY, I CAN HANDLE IT, BUDDY.
DON'T YOU FORGET THAT.

1881
01:31:44,695 --> 01:31:45,826
ALRIGHT. LET'S GET GOING, THEN.

1882
01:31:45,870 --> 01:31:46,871
[LAUGHING]

1883
01:31:46,914 --> 01:31:48,438
ONWARD AND UPWARD.

1884
01:31:48,481 --> 01:32:02,843
[LIGHT-HEARTED MUSIC]

1885
01:32:02,887 --> 01:32:06,238
BARTENDER SAYS, "SO, DIDN'T YOU
HAVE ANYTHING IN YOUR HAND?"

1886
01:32:06,282 --> 01:32:07,413
HE SAID, "YEAH," HE SAID.

1887
01:32:07,457 --> 01:32:09,633
"I HAD MRS. MCCORKLE'S LEFT TIT

1888
01:32:09,676 --> 01:32:11,156
BUT IT AIN'T WORTH A SHIT
IN A FIGHT."

1889
01:32:11,200 --> 01:32:23,125
[RAUCOUS LAUGHING]

1890
01:32:23,168 --> 01:32:26,737
JUST THEN THE MUSIC QUIT.

1891
01:32:26,780 --> 01:32:29,305
AND IT WENT, 'RIP!'

1892
01:32:29,348 --> 01:32:31,176
AND EVERYBODY TURNED AROUND
AND LOOKED AT OUR TABLE

1893
01:32:31,220 --> 01:32:34,919
AND I TURNED AROUND AND I SAID
TO THIS GUY, [LAUGHTER]

1894
01:32:34,962 --> 01:32:36,138
AND THEN THE MUSIC STARTED!

1895
01:32:36,181 --> 01:32:38,270
HE SAID,
"YOU DIRTY SON OF A BITCH!"

1896
01:32:40,968 --> 01:32:42,013
PLEASE DON'T GO!

1897
01:32:43,928 --> 01:32:47,323
[LAUGHTER]

1898
01:32:47,366 --> 01:32:49,325
WILL YOU QUIT HORSING AROUND,
WE'RE WASTING FILM HERE.

1899
01:32:49,368 --> 01:32:55,287
WASTING FILM.
THERE'S NO FILM IN THAT CAMERA!

1900
01:32:55,331 --> 01:32:58,856
YOU KNOW WE'RE --
I SHUT IT OFF AND I HIT SOMEONE.

1901
01:32:58,899 --> 01:33:02,599
IT HELPS IF YOU DON'T
JERK AROUND SO MUCH.

1902
01:33:02,642 --> 01:33:04,731
WELL, IT DOESN'T HELP
WHEN YOU'RE SHAKY, EITHER.

1903
01:33:04,775 --> 01:33:06,124
WELL, THAT'S WHAT I MEAN.

1904
01:33:06,168 --> 01:33:09,606
AW, SHIT! SEE, I DID IT AGAIN.
FUCK IT!

1905
01:33:09,649 --> 01:33:12,130
YOU BRING UP SOMETHING RELEVANT,

1906
01:33:12,174 --> 01:33:13,697
SOMETHING WE CAN
REALLY TALK ABOUT

1907
01:33:13,740 --> 01:33:16,700
THAT MAKES SOME GODDAMNED SENSE
INSTEAD OF PISSING ME OFF.

1908
01:33:16,743 --> 01:33:20,660
TIME AFTER TIME YOU BRING UP
THIS NONSENSE SHIT.

1909
01:33:26,753 --> 01:33:30,148
BOB! BOB! [LAUGHING]

1910
01:33:30,192 --> 01:33:31,802
COOL IT.

1911
01:33:31,845 --> 01:33:33,543
YOU WERE RUNNING A LITTLE LATE.
LOOK YOU'RE NOT EVEN DRESSED.

1912
01:33:33,586 --> 01:33:34,631
I REALIZE THAT.

1913
01:33:34,674 --> 01:33:35,632
YOU NEED TO GET DRESSED.

1914
01:33:35,675 --> 01:33:36,589
I'M GETTING OUT OF HERE.

1915
01:33:36,633 --> 01:33:37,460
THAT DIDN'T COME OUT RIGHT.

1916
01:33:37,503 --> 01:33:38,417
IT'S OKAY!

1917
01:33:38,461 --> 01:33:39,331
DUMB SHIT.

1918
01:33:39,375 --> 01:33:40,941
[LAUGHING]

1919
01:33:40,985 --> 01:33:43,161
I DON'T WANT TO HEAR ANYTHING
MORE ABOUT YOUR GIRLFRIENDS.

1920
01:33:43,205 --> 01:33:44,989
I DON'T NEED TO KNOW
HER WORLD OR HER HISTORY.

1921
01:33:45,032 --> 01:33:47,209
WELL, SAD VIOLIN MUSIC.

1922
01:33:47,252 --> 01:33:50,168
GET ON THE BALL.

1923
01:33:50,212 --> 01:33:54,346
ALRIGHT, I'M THROUGH.
 [LAUGHING]

1924
01:33:54,390 --> 01:33:55,478
HOLD THAT.

1925
01:33:55,521 --> 01:33:56,653
YEAH.
GET THAT SUCKER OPEN.

1926
01:33:56,696 --> 01:33:57,784
HAVE YOU EVER DONE
THIS BEFORE, BOB?

1927
01:33:57,828 --> 01:33:59,221
I'VE DONE IT LOTS OF TIMES.

1928
01:33:59,264 --> 01:34:01,571
BUT, YOU KNOW, EACH
ONE IS DIFFERENT.

1929
01:34:01,614 --> 01:34:03,399
DID YOU KNOW THAT?

1930
01:34:03,442 --> 01:34:04,878
IT'S KIND OF LIKE WOMAN.

1931
01:34:04,922 --> 01:34:08,839
USUALLY, I GET MY TEETH
ON THERE BUT I'M A LITTLE SHY.

1932
01:34:08,882 --> 01:34:12,147
ONE TIME I REALLY GOT BURNED.

1933
01:34:12,190 --> 01:34:14,192
I'LL HANG ON TO IT.
YOU TWIST IT.

1934
01:34:14,236 --> 01:34:15,411
AH?
YOU WANT ME TO TAKE THAT OFF?

1935
01:34:15,454 --> 01:34:17,239
YEAH.
TWIST THAT SUCKER.

1936
01:34:17,282 --> 01:34:17,935
OKAY.

